Books I finished on our trip! Reviews below 🌸

House of Sky and Breath 
5 ⭐️ (technically started this before my trip and finished while i was there haha) so many big events and things I didn’t predict. And that ending!!!! 🤯 Sooo excited to see how things will come together in future books. Can’t wait! 

Destroy Me (novella)
4 ⭐️ this felt like a necessary novella to the story. Still unsure about this series but l’m glad I saw Warner’s perspective. 

The Unhooneymooners 
3⭐️ Fun, cute, vacation read but something was missing for me. There was one thing about the love interest I couldn’t get past…

Book Lovers 
4.5 ⭐️ loved the banter and the romance but also loved the sister relationship aspect just as much as the romance. Very cute book!

May book reviews below 📖

Unravel Me - 3.75⭐️
a small step up from Shatter Me! I gained a lot more interest in the characters and story in general in this book but still not dying over it. I don’t love Juliette but other characters are telling me to keep giving it a chance!

Mexican Gothic - 4 ⭐️ 
my first horror-ish read! Spooky, gothic setting (love) with mysterious things happening.. with a strange twist… but it’s still able to keep up with the thrilling pace 

Ignite Me - 3.75 ⭐️ 
these books are just not leaving a lasting impression on me and I heard this is the best one? Bringing my previous ratings down to 3.5s 😭  Maybe I’m missing something?? Might not finish the rest of the series 😕

Icebreaker - 4.5 ⭐️ 
my favorite romance i’ve read so far! I did not expect to like a sports romance this much. Nathan is my type of book bf. 😩 all the other characters are so sweet too. I want my own house full of hockey players like them. very spiceyyyy

The Housemaid - 4.5 ⭐️ 
This book was very fun! I loved the twists and always wanted to know what was going to happen next. It had some predictable moments but it had me hooked and entertained the whole book! I’m unsure about where the second book is going haha 

Rock Paper Scissors - 4.5 ⭐️ 
I loved this! love the writing, love the thrills,  love the mystery, love the twists that just kept coming, loved the ending! One of my favorite books this month.
